José Carlos 

MINISTER OF HEALTH WITHOUT TECHNICAL KNOWLEDGE: Coronavirus
Eduardo Pazuello was warned that the pandemic could last up to 2 years in Brazil
The interim Minister of Health was alerted by a technical committee to the benefits of social isolation to reduce the impact of the pandemic on health and the economy. But - contrary to the alert - Pazuello guides the opening of activities when Brazil already has more than one million cases. The news was published by Estadão and confirmed by GloboNews.
